    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>See minister for foreign affairs and minister for colonies and urge the
                    imperative necessity of putting in force the definitive repertory at once.
                    Report fully and follow instructions as elaborated in my hundred and eight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
